Restrictions on certain activities have now been eased under level two regulations. JOHANNESBURG - South Africa will enter lockdown level two from Tuesday. Restrictions on certain activities have now been eased under level 2 regulations. The National Coronavirus Command Council, led by Cooperative Governance and Traditional Affairs Minister Nkosazana Dlamini-Zuma outlined activities permitted and prohibited under level two regulations. READ: Tobacco industry fired up and ready to roll Under the new regulations, only a maximum of 50 people are allowed at funerals, weddings, gyms, swimming pools, bars, taverns, shebeens, cinemas, theatres and concert venues. Here is a list of what is permitted and prohibited under level 2 regulations; PERMITTED  PROHIBITED - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs. The Minister of Cooperative Governance and Traditional Affairs, Dr Nkosazana Dlamini Zuma leads the briefing.